[23:13] <kid51> From what I can tell by reading the INSTRUCTIONS section in README.pod, if you want to install Parrot in the same location but in a different configuration, you should only need to call 'perl Configure.pl' again with different options, then make, make test, make install.
[23:15] <kid51> If you want to install it in a different location ... well, that may be more difficult.
[23:16] <kid51> In the sense that many applications which one builds from source code do not come with a 'make uninstall' target -- and Parrot is no different there.
